4.Sequence-based animations for dashboards:-
-Sequence-based animation means multiple animations run in a specific order, where one animation starts after or during another, creating a structured visual flow. 
Instead of everything animating at once, elements appear step-by-step.
This technique is widely used in dashboards, landing pages, onboarding flows, and data visualizations to guide user attention.
-Sequence-based animations organize UI motion so elements animate in a planned order, improving clarity, usability, and visual storytelling.
This is a supper simple React library that lets us create animations in an easy and straight forward manner.
The idea behind this library was to create animations that can be controlled very easily.
-Sequence-based animations example:-
//App.js
import React from "react";
import SequenceAnimatorExample from "./SequenceAnimatorExample";

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Sequence Animation</h2>
      <SequenceAnimatorExample />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;

//index.js
import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";
import App from "./App";

const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
root.render(<App />);

//SequenceAnimatorExample.js
import React from "react";
import { SequenceAnimator } from "react-sequence-animator";
import cat1 from "./statics/cat1.png";
import cat2 from "./statics/cat2.png";
import cat3 from "./statics/cat3.png";
import cat4 from "./statics/cat4.png";

class SequenceAnimatorExample extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <SequenceAnimator>
        <img src={cat1} alt="cat1"/>
        <img src={cat2} alt="cat2"/>
        <img src={cat3} alt="cat3"/>
        <img src={cat4} alt="cat4"/>
        
      </SequenceAnimator>
    );
  }
}

export default SequenceAnimatorExample;


